FLORIDA
</P>
<P>
In Florida, a key battleground state, Democratic educator Betty
Castor is in a neck-and-neck battle with Republican Mel Martinez, the
former Secretary of Housing and Urban Development in the George W.
Bush administration.
</P>
<P>
If he wins, Martinez (along with Colorado's Salazar, should the
Democrat prevail in Colorado) would be the first Hispanic in the
Senate in many years.
</P>
<P>
Recent polls haven states to stump for Democratic presidential
